                     </persName>
                     
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18311201-274-person2072">
                  MATTHEW 
                  RUTHERFORD
               <interp inst="t18311201-274-person2072" type="surname" value="RUTHERFORD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-274-person2072" type="given" value="MATTHEW"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-274-person2072" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18311201-274-viclabel1459" type="occupation">seaman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-274-victim2071 t18311201-274-viclabel1459"></join>; I had been to the Commons, and received my wages on the 2nd of December, and met the prisoner in a coffee-shop in <placeName id="t18311201-274-crimeloc1460">Ratcliff-highway</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18311201-274-crimeloc1460" type="placeName" value="Ratcliff-highway"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18311201-274-crimeloc1460" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-274-off1457 t18311201-274-crimeloc1460"></join>, between one and two o'clock the next morning: I had then fourteen sovereigns, and I changed one - I was not sober when I got to the coffee-shop; I found the prisoner there: she accosted me - she asked for something to drink - I gave her half a crown: she got some rum, and brought me three sixpences in change - I then went with her to her own house: I was there a quarter of an hour or twenty minutes; I counted my money in her house, but I did not give her any thing: I had nothing to do with her - she put her hands into my pocket, when I sat down on the chair; I said, "This will not do for me;" I got up and counted my money, I found I had still my thirteen sovereigns, and I put them all safe into my left-hand breeches pocket; I bade her good night, and was going down - as soon as I got to the stair-head, she came and put her hand into my pocket; I seized her hand, and got eight sovereigns out of it - she got off with the rest and went out; I went out of the house in about five minutes, and found her in custody; I had not given her any money.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18311201-274-person2073">
                  JAMES 
                  GRAHAM
               <interp inst="t18311201-274-person2073" type="surname" value="GRAHAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-274-person2073" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-274-person2073" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Police-constable. I heard a noise, and hastened to the place; I heard the prisoner run up some steps a little way from the house - she said, "Oh God! I have lost my shoe;" she came running towards me; I had a lamp in front of me - I turned the light on, and saw one of her hands grasped; I caught at it, and, to the best of my belief, I heard three sovereigns fall - I then searched her, and found two half-crowns and three sixpences in her bosom; I searched the place and so did others, but we found no sovereigns; the prosecutor said,"That is the girl that robbed me of five sovereigns, two half-crowns, and three sixpences."</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Did I not tell you, that he gave me two half-crowns and three sixpences? A. No, you never said any such thing; another officer found 8 1/2d. in her pocket.</p>

               <p>The prisoner put in a written Defence, stating that the prosecutor had given her the money.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18311201-274-verdict1461" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18311201-274-verdict1461" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 38. - <rs id="t18311201-274-punish1462" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18311201-274-punish1462" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-274-defend2069 t18311201-274-punish1462"></join>
               Transported for Fourteen Years
            </rs>.</p>
